# lodor#7 one-disc-per-launch: filling a 0-byte .m3u stub via --download lands disc 1
# (the engine's disc-1-first fill). The SAME launch must NOT also fire --fetch-next-disc
# — later discs arrive on relaunches / the daemon prefetch, not two-per-launch.
desc fetch hook (lodor#7): stub .m3u fill does not chain a same-launch next-disc fetch
invoke prehook
config paired
romarg Roms/PlayStation (PS)/✘ FF7.m3u
sdfile Roms/PlayStation (PS)/✘ FF7.m3u
engine 0|RESULT downloaded=1 discs_total=2 discs_present=1 discs_fetched=1
engine 0|
expect_exit 0
expect_trace ENGINE --download
expect_trace_absent ENGINE --fetch-next-disc
